modules.description: Tracks executed code paths during tests by instrumenting OCaml source files with coverage markers. Processes coverage data to generate detailed reports highlighting untested functions and branches. Integrates with build systems to automate coverage analysis and test validation.

Handles coverage instrumentation by setting up tag-based tracking and integrates with the build system via a hook handler. Operates on build hooks and coverage tags defined by the OCamlbuild plugin interface. Used to enable test coverage collection during build processes.
